 Limited Company Accounts 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 Limited Company Accounts Business
 operating through limited company must prepare and file their limited company accounts 
to companies house and HMRC in a statuary format.  At K & M Accountants Luton, we 
believe that an accountant's job is not just preparing the accounts in a 
acceptable format but to provide client with a proactive advice about 
their business. We at K & M Accountants strongly believe that 
accountant should not wait for client to ask but instead must always 
lead from front by providing solutions upfront. After all  ' Our success is in your success'  Therefore all of our clients receive key financial and non financial 
information about their business such as 1) Key Margins 2) Reason for 
low/high margins 3) Ways to improve margin 4) Detailed comparative analysis 
with previous years figures and industry average 5) Help setting up 
targets 6) Help identifying ways to reduce cost and improve profitability 7) Detailed balance sheet analysis including business liquidity and 
sustainability. 8) Ways to improve staff efficiency through motivation For more information please  contact us  or email us at accounts@kandmaccountants.co.uk   
